24/03/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government has approved a national tourism programme dubbed "Super Ski in the Carpathians".
The state news agency Rompres reports Monday (24 March) that specialists in the tourism sector will first identify attractive locations for winter sports, then draft investment plans.
The ministries of tourism and sports will work together to establish investment partnerships between central and local public entities and private companies.
The first stage of the project will cover the districts of Prahova Valley and the Upper Valley of Teleajen.
(Rompres, Adriana Advertising - 24/03/03)
